obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (21634)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21634&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Security Act, 1980.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (21635)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21635&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate Government" means, as respects a detention order made by the Central`
  line `Government or a person detained under such order, the Central Government, and as respects a`
  line `detention order made by a State Government or by an officer subordinate to a State Government or as`
  line `respects a person detained under such order, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) "detention order" means an order made under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "foreigner" has the same meaning as in the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946);`
  line
  line `(d) "person" includes a foreigner;`
  line
  line `(e) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (21636)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to make orders detaining certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21636&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government or the State`
  line `Government may,—`
  line
  line `(a) if satisfied with respect to any person that with a view to preventing him from acting in any`
  line `manner prejudicial to the defence of India, the relations of India with foreign powers, or the security`
  line `of India, or`
  line
  line `(b) if satisfied with respect to any foreigner that with a view to regulating his continued presence`
  line `in India or with a view to making arrangements for his expulsion from India,`
  line
  line `it is necessary so to do, make an order directing that such person be detained.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the State Government may, if satisfied with respect to any person that`
  line `with a view to preventing him from acting in any manner prejudicial to the security of the State or from`
  line `acting in any manner prejudicial to the maintenance of Public order or from acting in any manner`
  line `prejudicial to the maintenance of supplies and services essential to the community it is necessary so to do,`
  line `make an order directing that such person be detained.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, "acting in any manner prejudicial to the`
  line `maintenance of supplies and services essential to the community" does not include "acting in any manner`
  line `prejudicial to the maintenance of supplies of commodities essential to the community" as defined in the`
  line `Explanation to sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Prevention of Blackmarketing and Maintenance of`
  line `Supplies of Essential Commodities Act, 1980 (7 of 1980), and accordingly, no order of detention shall be`
  line `made under this Act on any ground on which an order of detention may be made under that Act.`
  line
  line `(3) If, having regard to the circumstances prevailing or likely to prevail in any area within the local`
  line `limits of the jurisdiction of a District Magistrate or a Commissioner of Police, the State Government is`
  line `satisfied that it is necessary so to do, it may, by order in writing, direct, that during such period as may be`
  line `specified in the order, such District Magistrate or Commissioner of Police may also, if satisfied as`
  line `provided in sub-section (2), exercise the powers conferred by the said sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period specified in an order made by the State Government under this sub-section`
  line `shall not, in the first instance, exceed three months, but the State Government may, if satisfied as aforesaid that it is necessary so to do, amend such order to extend such period from time to time by any`
  line `period not exceeding three months at any one time.`
  line
  line `(4) When any order is made under this section by an officer mentioned in sub-section (3), he shall`
  line `forthwith report the fact to the State Government to which he is subordinate together with the grounds on`
  line `which the order has been made and such other particulars as, in his opinion, have a bearing on the matter,`
  line `and no such order shall remain in force for more than twelve days after the making thereof unless, in the`
  line `meantime, it has been approved by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where under section 8 the grounds of detention are communicated by the officer making`
  line `the order after five days but not later than ^1`
  line `[fifteen days] from the date of detention, this sub-section shall`
  line `apply subject to the modification that, for the words "twelve days", the words`
  line ^2
  line `"[twenty days]" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `(5) When any order is made or approved by the State Government under this section, the State`
  line `Government shall, within seven days, report the fact to the Central Government together with the grounds`
  line `on which the order has been made and such other particulars as, in the opinion of the State Government,`
  line `have a bearing on the necessity for the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1984, s. 3, for "ten days" (w.e.f. 5-4-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "fifteen days" (w.e.f. 5-4-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (21637)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Execution of detention orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21637&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A detention order may be executed at any place in India in the`
  line `manner provided for the execution of warrants of arrest under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (21638)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to regulate place and conditions of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21638&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every person in respect of whom a`
  line `detention order has been made shall be liable—`
  line
  line `(a) to be detained in such place and under such conditions, including conditions as to`
  line `maintenance, discipline and punishment for breaches of discipline, as the appropriate Government`
  line `may, by general or special order, specify; and`
  line
  line `(b) to be removed from one place of detention to another place of detention, whether within the`
  line `same State or in another State, by order of the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made by a State Government under clause (b) for the removal of a`
  line `person from one State to another State except with the consent of the Government of that other State.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (21639)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Grounds of detention severable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-6-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21639&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Grounds of detention severable.—Where a person has been detained in pursuance of an order`
  line `of detention whether made before or after the commencement of the National Security (Second`
  line `Amendment) Act, 1984 (60 of 1984)] under section 3 which has been made on two or more grounds, such`
  line `order of detention shall be deemed to have been made separately on each of such grounds and`
  line accordingly—
  line
  line `(a) such order shall not be deemed to be invalid or inoperative merely because one or some of the`
  line `grounds is or are—`
  line
  line `(i) vague,`
  line
  line `(ii) non-existent,`
  line
  line `(iii) not relevant,`
  line
  line `(iv) not connected or not proximately connected with such person, or`
  line
  line `(v) invalid for any other reason whatsoever,`
  line
  line `and it is not, therefore, possible to hold that the Government or officer making such order would have`
  line `been satisfied as provided in section 3 with reference to the remaining ground or grounds and made`
  line `the order of detention;`
  line
  line `(b) the Government or officer making the order of detention shall be deemed to have made the`
  line `order of detention under the said section after being satisfied as provided in that section with`
  line `reference to the remaining ground or grounds.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (21640)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Detention orders not to be invalid or inoperative on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21640&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No detention order shall`
  line `be invalid or inoperative merely by reason—`
  line
  line `(a) that the person to be detained thereunder is outside the limits of the territorial jurisdiction of`
  line `the Government or officer making the order, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the place of detention of such person is outside the said limits.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (21641)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers in relation to absconding persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21641&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government or an officer mentioned in sub-section (3) of section 3, as the case may be, has reason to`
  line `believe that a person in respect of whom a detention order has been made has absconded or is concealing`
  line `himself so that the order cannot be executed, that Government or officer may—`
  line
  line `(a) make a report in writing of the fact to a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of`
  line `the first class having jurisdiction in the place where the said person ordinarily resides;`
  line
  line `(b) by order notified in the Official Gazette direct the said person to appear before such officer, at`
  line `such place and within such period as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the making of a report against any person under clause (a) of sub-section (1), the provisions`
  line `of sections 82, 83, 84 and 85 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall apply in respect`
  line `of such person and his property as if the detention order made against him were a warrant issued by the`
  line Magistrate.
  line
  line `(3) If any person fails to comply with an order issued under clause (b) of sub-section (1), he shall,`
  line `unless he proves that it was not possible for him to comply therewith and that he had, within the period`
  line `specified in the order, informed the officer mentioned in the order of the reason which rendered`
  line `compliance therewith impossible and of his whereabouts, be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every`
  line `offence under sub-section (3) shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (21642)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Grounds of order of detention to be disclosed to persons affected by the order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 24 of 1984, s. 4, for "ten days" (w.e.f. 5-4-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21642&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a`
  line `person is detained in pursuance of a detention order, the authority making the order shall, as soon as may`
  line `be, but ordinarily not later than five days and in exceptional circumstances and for reasons to be recorded`
  line `in writing, not later than ^1`
  line `[fifteen days] from the date of detention, communicate to him the grounds on`
  line `which the order has been made and shall afford him the earliest opportunity of making a representation`
  line `against the order to the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall require the authority to disclose facts which it considers to be`
  line `against the public interest to disclose.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (21643)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Constitution of Advisory Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21643&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government and each State Government`
  line `shall, whenever necessary, constitute one or more Advisory Boards for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such Board shall consist of three persons who are, or have been, or are qualified to be`
  line `appointed as, Judges of a High Court, and such persons shall be appointed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government shall appoint one of the members of the Advisory Board who is, or`
  line `has been, a Judge of a High Court to be its Chairman, and in the case of a Union territory, the`
  line `appointment to the Advisory Board of any person who is a Judge of the High Court of a State shall be`
  line `with the previous approval of the State Government concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (21644)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Reference to Advisory Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21644&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, in every case`
  line `where a detention order has been made under this Act, the appropriate Government shall, within three`
  line `weeks from the date of detention of a person under the order, place before the Advisory Board constituted`
  line `by it under section 9, the grounds on which the order has been made and the representation, if any, made`
  line `by the person affected by the order, and in case where the order has been made by an officer mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 3, also the report by such officer under sub-section (4) of that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (21645)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Procedure of Advisory Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21645&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Advisory Board shall, after considering the materials`
  line `placed before it and, after calling for such further information as it may deem necessary from the`
  line `appropriate Government or from any person called for the purpose through the appropriate Government`
  line `or from the person concerned, and if, in any particular case, it considers it essential so to do or if the`
  line `person concerned desires to be heard, after hearing him in person, submit its report to the appropriate`
  line `Government within seven weeks from the date of detention of the person concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) The report of the Advisory Board shall specify in a separate part thereof the opinion of the`
  line `Advisory Board as to whether or not there is sufficient cause for the detention of the person concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) When there is a difference of opinion among the members forming the Advisory Board, the`
  line `opinion of the majority of such members shall be deemed to be the opinion of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall entitle any person against whom a detention order has been made to`
  line `appear by any legal practitioner in any matter connected with the reference to the Advisory Board; and`
  line `the proceedings of the Advisory Board and its report, excepting that part of the report in which the`
  line `opinion of the Advisory Board is specified, shall be confidential.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (21646)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Action upon the report of the Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21646&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any case where the Advisory Board has`
  line `reported that there is, in its opinion, sufficient cause for the detention of a person, the appropriate`
  line `Government may confirm the detention order and continue the detention of the person concerned for such`
  line `period as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) In any case where the Advisory Board has reported that there is, in its opinion, no sufficient cause`
  line `for the detention of a person, the appropriate Government shall revoke the detention order and cause the`
  line `person concerned to be released forthwith.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (21647)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Maximum period of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21647&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The maximum period for which any person may be detained in`
  line `pursuance of any detention order which has been confirmed under section 12 shall be twelve months from`
  line `the date of detention:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the power of the appropriate Government`
  line `to revoke or modify the detention order at any earlier time.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (21648)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Revocation of detention orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1984, s. 3, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 21-6-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21648&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 21 of the`
  line `General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), a detention order may, at any time, be revoked or modified,—`
  line
  line `(a) notwithstanding that the order has been made by an officer mentioned in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 3, by the State Government to which that officer is subordinate or by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding that the order has been made by a State Government, by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) The expiry or revocation of a detention order (hereafter in this sub-section referred to as the`
  line `earlier detention order) shall not whether such earlier detention order has been made before or after the`
  line `commencement of the National Security (Second Amendment) Act, 1984 (60 of 1984)] bar the making of`
  line `another detention order (hereafter in this sub-section referred to as the subsequent detention order) under`
  line `section 3 against the same person:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case where no fresh facts have arisen after the expiry or revocation of the earlier`
  line `detention order made against such person, the maximumperiod for which such person may be detained in`
  line `pursuance of the subsequent detention order shall, in no case, extend beyond the expiry of a period of`
  line `twelve months from the date of detention under the earlier detention order.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (21649)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 16
  title `Circumstances in which persons may be detained for periods longer than three months without obtaining the opinion of Advisory Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21649&sectionno=14A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Circumstances in which persons may be detained for periods longer than three months without obtaining the opinion of Advisory Boards.—(1) Nothwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Act, or in any judgment, decree or order of any court or other authority, any`
  line `person in respect of whom an order of detention has been made under this Act at any time before the^2`
  line [8th
  line `day of June, 1989] may be detained without obtaining the opinion of the Advisory Board for a period`
  line `longer than three months, but not exceeding six months, from the date of his detention where such person`
  line `had been detained with a view to preventing him, in any disturbed area—`
  line
  line `(i) from interfering with the efforts of Government in coping with the terrorist and disruptive`
  line `activities; and`
  line
  line `(ii) from acting in any manner prejudicial to—`
  line
  line `(a) thedefence of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) the security of India; or`
  line
  line `(c) the security of the State; or`
  line
  line `(d) the maintenance of public order; or`
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance of supplies and services essential to the community.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—The provisions of the Explanation to sub-section (2) of section 3 shall apply for the`
  line `purposes of this sub-section as they apply for the purposes of that sub-section.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—In this sub-section, "disturbed area" means any area which is for the time being`
  line `declared by notification under section 3 of the Punjab Disturbed Areas Act, 1983 (32 of 1983), or under`
  line `section 3 of the Chandigarh Disturbed Areas Act, 1983 (33 of 1983), to be a disturbed area.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.—In this sub-section, "terrorist and disruptive activities" means "terrorist acts" and`
  line `"disruptive activities" within the meaning of the Terrorist and Disruptive Activities (Prevention)`
  line `Ordinance, 1987 (Ord. 2 of 1987).`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any person to whom sub-section (1) applies, sections 3, 8 and 10 to 14 shall have`
  line `effect subject to the following modifications, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) in section 3,—`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (4), in the proviso,—`
  line
  line `(A) for the words "ten days", the words "fifteen days" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(B) for the words "fifteen days" the words "twenty days" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (5), for the words "seven days", the words "fifteen days" shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(b) in section 8, in sub-section (1), for the words "ten days", the words "fifteen days" shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(c) in section 10, for the words "shall, within three weeks", the words "shall, within four months`
  line `and two weeks" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(d) in section 11,—`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), for the words "seven weeks", the words "five months and three weeks"`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2), for the words "detention of the person concerned", the words`
  line `"continued detention of the person concerned" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(e) in section 12, for the words "for the detention", at both the places where they occur, the words`
  line `"for the continued detention" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(f) in section 13, for the words "twelve months", the words "two years" shall be substituted:`
  line
  line `(g) in section 14, in the proviso to sub-section (2), for the words "twelve months" the words "two`
  line `years" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1987, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9-6-1987) earlier section 14A was inserted vide the National Security (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1984 (24 of 1984), s. 5 and subsequently the said section was repealed by the National Security (Amendment) Act, 1987`
  line `(27 of 1987), s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 43 of 1988, s. 2, for "8th day of June, 1988" (w.e.f. 26-5-1988)`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (21650)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Temporary release of persons detained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21650&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, at any time,`
  line `direct that any person detained in pursuance of a detention order may be released for any specified period`
  line `either without conditions or upon such conditions specified in the direction as that person accepts, and`
  line `may, at any time, cancel his release.`
  line
  line `(2) In directing the release of any person under sub-section (1), the appropriate Government may`
  line `require him to enter into a bond with or without sureties for the due observance of the conditions specified`
  line `in the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person released under sub-section (1) shall surrender himself at the time and place, and to the`
  line `authority, specified in the order directing his release or cancelling his release, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) If any person fails without sufficient cause to surrender himself in the manner specified in`
  line `sub-section (3), he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(5) If any person released under sub-section (1) fails to fulfil any of the conditions imposed upon him`
  line `under the said sub-section or in the bond entered into by him, the bond shall be declared to be forfeited`
  line `and any person bound thereby shall be liable to pay the penalty thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (21651)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21651&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Central Government or a State Government, and no suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any person, for anything in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (21652)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Act not to have effect with respect to detentions under State laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21652&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act`
  line `shall apply or have any effect with respect to orders of detention, made under any State law, which are in`
  line `force immediately before the commencement of the National Security Ordinance, 1980 (11 of 1980), and`
  line `accordingly every person in respect of whom an order of detention made under any State law is in force`
  line `immediately before such commencement, shall be governed with respect to such detention by the`
  line `provisions of such State law or where the State law under which such order of detention is made is an`
  line `Ordinance (hereinafter referred to as the State Ordinance) promulgated by the Governor of that State and`
  line `the State Ordinance has been replaced—`
  line
  line `(i) before such commencement, by an enactment passed by the Legislature of that State, by such`
  line `enactment; or`
  line
  line `(ii) after such commencement, by an enactment which is passed by the Legislature of that State`
  line `and the application of which is confined to orders of detention made before such commencement`
  line `under the State Ordinance, by such enactment,`
  line
  line `as if this Act had not been enacted.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to bar the making under section 3, of a detention order`
  line `against any person referred to in sub-section (1) after the detention order in force in respect of him as`
  line `aforesaid immediately before the commencement of the National Security Ordinance, 1980 (11 of 1980),`
  line `ceases to have effect for any reason whatsoever.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, "State law" means any law providing for preventive`
  line `detention on all or any of the grounds on which an order of detention may be made under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 3 and in force in any State immediately before the commencement of the said Ordinance.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (21653)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254&sectionId=21653&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00019_198065_1517807325254
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Security Ordinance, 1980 (11 of 1980), is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act, as if this Act had`
  line `come into force on the 23rd day of September, 1980, and, in particular, any reference made under section`
  line `10 of the said Ordinance and pending before any Advisory Board immediately before the date on which`
  line `this Act receives the assent of the President may continue to be dealt with by that Board after that date as`
  line `if such Board had been constituted under section 9 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
